:: Outcast Village Settlement Layer1[layer1 nobr hub]
<<PassTimeWithEvents>>
<<if !setup.passingTime()>>
	<<CarryAdjust>><<checkTime>>

	As you wander through Outcast Village, the air buzzes with a vibrant, communal energy, residents with Curse-marked features greet each other warmly in the streets. Despite the village's name, there's a palpable sense of unity and acceptance here. <br><br>
	<<if $visitSL1 === 0>>
		<img src="images/Habitation/outcastvillage.png" width=70%><br>
		<<set $visitSL1 += 1>>
		<<set _settleTemp = 8>>
	<<elseif $visitSL1 === 1>>
		<<set $visitSL1 += 1>>
		<<set _settleTemp = 18>>
	<<else>>
		<<set _settleTemp = random(0,20)>>
	<</if>>
	<<if _settleTemp === 1>>
	You marvel at the hustle and bustle this small community seems to provide. Everywhere around you, people are busy at work or having conversations with one another. The atmosphere seems rather pleasant, despite the isolated location, as if the people here are happy with the way things are. <br><br>
	<<elseif _settleTemp === 2>>
	Near the village's outskirts, you notice a heated debate among a group of villagers. They're discussing the potential introduction of hydroelectric generators to Outcast Village. One side argues passionately for the benefits of electricity, envisioning a future where the village thrives with new technological advancements. The opposing side, equally fervent, advocates for preserving the village's rustic charm, fearing that too much change might disrupt the close-knit community and the simple life they've come to cherish. The debate continues, without any clear conclusion. It's clear opinion is split on the issue.<br><br>
	<<elseif _settleTemp === 3>>
	As you wander through the dimly lit streets of Outcast Village, a curious sight catches your eye. A tall figure, adorned with delicate moth wings that flutter gently, stands before a small crowd, spinning tales of ancient Abyss legends. The storyteller's captivating voice seems to enchant his listeners, who hang onto every word. His tales are a mix of heroism and tragedy. He tells of a hero that reaches down to the bottom of the sixth layer and finds endless splendor, but is unable to return due to the pressure of the miasma. Of course, if the hero was trapped there, how could anyone up here tell his story? But the story isn't about the hero, it's about the legend.<br><br>
	<<elseif _settleTemp === 4 && $hiredCompanions.some(e => e.id === setup.companionIds.khemia)>>
	<<say $rndM>>Hey, Khemia! Over here!<</say>><br>
	You and Khemia swivel, spotting a towering middle-aged man energetically beckoning from atop an in-progress building.
	<br><br>
	<<say $companionKhemia>>Hartman! Good to see you, man. How's life treating you?<</say>><br>
	<<say $rndM>>All good, all good. We're on the home stretch with the new barn! Really owe you one for the hand last time. Didn't expect to see you swinging back through so soon, and with a new crew no less?<</say>><br>
	<<say $companionKhemia>>Ah, you know how it goes. Last venture didn't quite pan out, but I've got a solid feeling about this team.<</say>><br>
	With a friendly slap on your back and a conspiratorial wink, he signals his confidence.<br><br>
	<<say $rndM>>Well, that's what I like to hear. Don't let me keep you folks. Catch you around!<</say>><br>
	He gives you a final cheerful wave and turns back to his labor.<br><br>
	<<elseif _settleTemp === 5 && $hiredCompanions.some(e => e.id === setup.companionIds.lily)>>
	Strolling through the village, you're greeted warmly by locals. Lily, with her boundless energy, responds with even greater enthusiasm.<br><br>
	<<say $companionLily>>Hi there! Hope you're having a great day!<</say>><br>
	The woman with striking orange eyes chuckles at Lily's exuberant greeting.<br><br>
	<<say $rndF>>Well hello, young one! Such unusual, beautiful eyes – they're quite the blessing for a Curse, wouldn't you say?<</say>><br>
	<<say $companionLily>>Hehe, thank you! But no Curse for me – these eyes are all-natural. Perks of being an angel!<</say>><br>
	A giggle escapes the woman at Lily's cheerful declaration.<br><br>
	<<say $rndF>>What a delightful companion you must be. Take care, and safe travels!<</say>><br>
	<<say $companionLily>>Thanks! See ya!<</say>><br>
	<<elseif _settleTemp === 6>>
	<<include "L1 Reactions">>
	<<elseif _settleTemp === 7 && $mc.hasCurse(HijinksEnsue)>>
	<<include "Hijinks Ensue Scenes">>
	<<elseif _settleTemp === 8>>
	On the outskirts of the village, beneath the canopy of the twilight sky, you spot a trio of figures sharing a quiet moment together. Two women and a man, each bearing distinctive marks of their journey into the Abyss - horns, glowing skin, and feathered wings, respectively - sit closely, intertwined. Their conversation, low and filled with laughter, pauses as they share a series of tender kisses and caresses. It's amazing how open they are with their affection here, compared to what you'd see on the surface.<br><br>
	<<elseif _settleTemp >= 18 - (1+$hiredCompanions.length) && _settleTemp < 19 && ($hiredCompanions.length > 0  || $ownedRelics.some(e => e.name === "Creepy Doll") )>>
	<<include "Companion Layer Interaction">>
	<<elseif _settleTemp >= 19>>
	<<include "Curse Descriptions">><br><br>
	<</if>>
	
