:: Bounty Board [nobr]
<<include "Bandit lookalike score">>
<<if $bountyboardvisit==false>>
    You approach a large wooden board adorned with a collection of wanted posters on the side of a weathered building.<br><br>
    <<say $Sheriff>>Interested in the bounty board, stranger?<</say>><br>
        
    You turn to see a grizzled local hefting a hunting rifle, a makeshift badge pinned to his chest. This must be the town's idea of law enforcement — the local sheriff.<br><br>
    <<if _changedAppearanceScore < 8 && ($PulseBloomUse == "The bandit" || $companionSwitched == $companionBandit.id)>>
            You spot the sheriff lounging in a chair beside the bounty board, his vacant stare snapping to attention as you approach. His jaw drops as he takes in your appearance. In an instant, his expression hardens and he levels his rifle at you. <br><br>
            <<say $Sheriff>> Well, if it ain't "Quickfingers" herself, come to turn herself in?<</say>><br>   
            Shocked, you raise your hands.<br><br>
            <<say $mc>> I don't...<</say>><br>
            Your gaze falls on the familiar wanted posters adorning the bounty board.<br><br>
            <<include "Wanted posters">>
            <<say $mc>> This is all a misunderstanding. I'm not her!<</say>><br>
            <<say $Sheriff>> Sure it ain't, darlin'. Now, face down on the ground, nice and easy. <</say>><br>
            Your mind races, searching for an escape.<br><br>
            <<say $mc>> Hold on! How can I be here if she's right over there?<</say>><br>
            <<say $Sheriff>> What're you talkin' about? <</say>><br>
            The moment the sheriff turns to look, you bolt, rounding the corner of the building at full sprint.<br><br>
            <<say $Sheriff>> Why, you little- <</say>><br>
            Gunshots ring out behind you. A searing pain erupts in your shoulder as if struck by a white-hot poker. The other shots miss their mark, and soon all you hear is distant cursing.<br>
