:: Bandit not turned in [nobr]
<<say $mc>>I'm sorry, but she stays with me for now.<</say>><br>
The sheriff's eyebrow arches high as he tightens his grip on his rifle.<br><br>
<<say $Sheriff>>Are you tellin' me you're harborin' and aidin' a known fugitive?<</say>><br>
<<say $mc>>It's not like that. I need to keep her in my custody for the time being. She's... crucial to my dive.<</say>><br>
The sheriff heaves a weary sigh, scratching the stubble on the back of his head.<br><br>
<<say $Sheriff>>If this is some peculiar diver nonsense, spare me the details. You lot get stranger by the day. I s'pose as long as she's with you, she ain't our problem.<</say>><br>
